th xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math> such as <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>13</mn></math>. <br>Award <em><strong>M1A0</strong></em> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>13</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"32212058","referenceCode":"24N.1.SL.TZ1.7c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Two Scottish Terriers are selected at random from a large population. Find the probability that both dogs have a mass less than 7.2 kg.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.6—Combined, mutually exclusive, conditional, independence, prob diagrams"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}